The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 July is 46,604 (5,394.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 July, there were 1,580 new confirmed cases (182.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 June, there were 824 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 92% (756 extra cases).
